  "text": "User Personas\n\n1. Olivia Chen — Operations Manager\n\t•\tBackground: 8+ years managing supply chain operations in a mid-sized manufacturing company.\n\t•\tGoals: Wants accurate forecasts to optimize inventory levels, minimize waste, and avoid stockouts.\n\t•\tFrustrations: Past tools were too rigid — she needs customization based on seasonal changes and anomalies.\n\n2. Daniel Ruiz — Financial Analyst\n\t•\tBackground: Junior financial analyst in a fast-scaling SaaS company.\n\t•\tGoals: Forecast subscription revenue churn and upsells to report realistic financial plans.\n\t•\tFrustrations: Overly volatile forecasts from AI tools that “overreact” to minor fluctuations.\n\n3. Priya Patel — Product Manager\n\t•\tBackground: PM for an AI-first logistics platform.\n\t•\tGoals: Integrate forecasting into her product to enable customers to predict delivery times and demand surges.\n\t•\tFrustrations: API-based tools without clean documentation or rate limits that throttle at peak times.\n\n⸻\n\nFunctional Requirements\n\nCore Forecasting\n\t•\tProvide time-series forecasting for numeric KPIs (inventory, revenue, usage metrics).\n\t•\tAllow users to input historical data manually or via integrations.\n\t•\tForecast horizon customizable: 7 days, 30 days, 90 days, 1 year.\n\t•\tModel selection: AutoML (default), with manual override options for ARIMA, Prophet, or LSTM models for advanced users.\n\nAlerting\n\t•\tThreshold-based alerts for forecasted metrics (e.g., stock expected to run out within 10 days).\n\t•\tSmart anomaly alerts: Detect deviations from forecasted trends automatically.\n\t•\tAlert delivery options: Email, SMS, Webhook.\n\nReporting\n\t•\tDaily, weekly, monthly forecast summary reports.\n\t•\tComparison reports: Forecast vs. Actual with deviation analysis.\n\t•\tExport formats: CSV, PDF, JSON.\n\n⸻\n\nNon‑Functional Requirements\n\nScalability\n\t•\tSupport 10,000+ simultaneous forecasts across multiple organizations.\n\t•\tHorizontal auto-scaling enabled via Kubernetes and container orchestration.\n\nAvailability\n\t•\t99.9% uptime target (measured monthly).\n\t•\tGraceful degradation: read-only mode if backend services are down.\n\nPerformance\n\t•\tForecast generation time must not exceed 5 seconds for <100,000 data points.\n\t•\tAlert processing latency under 1 second after data ingestion.\n\n⸻\n\nAI Sensitivity Slider\n\nDescription:\n\t•\tUsers adjust the “sensitivity” of forecasts using a simple slider:\n\t•\tConservative Mode (left side): Favors stability. Less responsive to minor data fluctuations.\n\t•\tVolatile Mode (right side): Hyper-reactive to recent changes, suitable for dynamic environments.\n\t•\tIntermediate states provide a weighted blend based on exponential smoothing factors.\n\t•\tDefault setting is Balanced at 50%.\n\nExample:\nOlivia managing seasonal inventory sets the slider toward Conservative during stable months, then shifts it toward Volatile during unpredictable seasons (e.g., Black Friday).\n\n⸻\n\nReporting & Dashboards\n\nRequired Visualizations\n\t•\tForecasted Trend Line (historical + prediction interval shading).\n\t•\tAnomaly Heatmaps.\n\t•\tDeviation Charts (Actual vs. Forecast).\n\t•\tAlert Frequency Graphs (over time).\n\t•\tSensitivity Distribution Graphs (to monitor slider usage impact).\n\nExport Options\n\t•\tScheduled email delivery of PDFs.\n\t•\tDirect download of CSVs with timestamps and confidence intervals.\n\t•\tEmbed charts via iframe or JS snippets into external dashboards (with auth).\n\n⸻\n\nIntegrations & API\n\nEndpoints\n\t•\t/api/forecast/upload – Upload historical data.\n\t•\t/api/forecast/generate – Trigger forecast computation.\n\t•\t/api/forecast/result – Retrieve forecast output.\n\t•\t/api/alerts/subscribe – Create new threshold-based alert.\n\t•\t/api/report/export – Generate downloadable reports.\n\nAuthentication\n\t•\tOAuth 2.0 with JWT access tokens.\n\t•\tAPI keys available for service-to-service integrations.\n\nRate Limits\n\t•\tFree tier: 100 API calls/hour.\n\t•\tPremium: 5,000 API calls/hour.\n\t•\tCustom enterprise plans available.\n\nWebhook Support\n\t•\tOutbound webhooks for real-time alert delivery to Slack, PagerDuty, custom endpoints.\n\n⸻\n\nSecurity & Compliance\n\nData Encryption\n\t•\tAt rest: AES-256 encryption on all stored data.\n\t•\tIn transit: TLS 1.3 enforced across all APIs and frontend apps.\n\nAudit Logs\n\t•\tImmutable audit logs capturing:\n\t•\tData upload events.\n\t•\tForecast generation requests.\n\t•\tAlert trigger events.\n\t•\tReport export activities.\n\t•\tLogs stored for minimum 1 year; configurable up to 5 years for enterprise customers.\n\nRegulatory Compliance\n\t•\tGDPR, CCPA, and SOC 2 Type II alignment.\n\t•\tRight-to-be-forgotten workflows enabled on request.",
